  { question: "What is an aspect ratio?", answer: "An aspect ratio is the proportional relationship between the width and height of a rectangle, expressed as two numbers separated by a colon (e.g., 16:9). It describes the shape of screens, images, and video frames. A 16:9 ratio means the width is 16 units for every 9 units of height." },
